The paper deals with issues related to intelligent data analysis and machine learning, which are core topics in computer science. The proposed scheme for synthesizing correct supervised classification procedures is a machine learning technique, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the dualization problem over products of partially ordered sets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of matrices in the formulation of the problem suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on model and real-life data, which indicates that it may also be relevant to the category of data science (cs.DS). Overall, the most likely category for this paper is machine learning (cs.LG), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data science (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
